<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-44-0944 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reports two case studies on 1) pillar load transfer and 2)subsidence, and their influence on mine ground stability. The investigationswere carried out by the US Bureau of Mines, Pennsylvania. All the conclusionsand design considerations discussed are based on actual underground measurementsperformed at two Appalachian coal mines. Alternative design and groundsupport considerations are discussed for both case studies. 10 figs.</TEXT></DOC>